{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὑπερηφᾰν-έω</b>, <br /> used by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] once in <i>participle</i>, much like{ὑπερηνορέων}, <b>overweening, arrogant,</b> ὑπερηφανέοντες Ἐπειοί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.694 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: hence later writers formed the Verb, <b>to be arrogant,</b> ἐπί τινας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Neh.9.10, compare 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιστολαί” 17, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.10.8, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ κακιῶν ί” p.11 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus, +others, 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 3.1.1, etc. \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> later writers also used it in a <i>transitive</i> sense, <b>treat disdainfully,</b> with <i>accusative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 23.15, 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 6.3.4, +others, 2nd c.AD(?): Xenophon Ephesius Scriptor Eroticus 1.16, “POxy.” 1676.16 (3rd c.AD)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>], etc.: with <i>genitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 21.249b, probably in 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 31 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, <b>scorn</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Longus Scriptor Eroticus 4.19. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> ὑ. ἑαυτούς <b>extol</b> themselves, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.33.8. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9548","accentedUnicode":"ὑπερηφανέω","shortDef":"be prideful; extol above others","mediumDef":"be prideful; extol above others","stepGloss":"be prideful","stepTransliteration":"huperēfaneō","_step_Type":"verb"}]}